                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A shadow drake spits a ball of black liquid that explodes into a cloud of frigid black shadow. This attack has a range of 40 feet and explodes in a 5-foot-radius burst. Creatures within the burst take [[/r 2d6 #cold]]{2d6 cold damage} (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"16\" data-pf2-traits=\"arcane,cold,evocation,shadow,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Shadow Breath DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save). The explosion of shadow also snuffs out mundane light sources the size of a torch, lantern, or smaller, and attempts to counteract magical light with a +8 counteract modifier.</p>\n<p data-visibility=\"gm\">The shadow drake can't use Shadow Breath again for [[/br 1d6]] rounds.</p>"
